      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Last-mile delivery is the final stage of the supply chain, covering the journey from a local depot to the customer's door, and it is where many costly errors tend to occur. As artificial intelligence becomes more widely used to manage routing, scheduling, and customer communications, new risks are emerging that teams need to understand. This lesson explores how AI-driven decisions can go wrong in practical delivery scenarios, including incorrect route suggestions, poorly timed deliveries, and automated messages that frustrate or mislead customers. You do not need a technical background to follow along, as the focus is on real-world situations and straightforward guidance. By the end of this lesson, you will be better equipped to spot potential AI-related problems in last-mile operations and take sensible steps to address them.",
